data.title: Contract Manufacturing in or near Arizona (AZ) on Thomasnet
data.meta_description: Contract Manufacturing Suppliers located in Arizona
data.text:
Contract manufacturing services for Inconel®, plastic, rubber, glass, composite, aluminum, brass, steel, stainless steel, and titanium. Capabilities include laser and waterjet cutting, bending, forming, and turning. Secondary services such as assembly, bending, brazing, broaching, inspection, plating, anodizing, and painting are offered. Prototype and low to high volume production run are available. Suitable for conveyors, consumer products, broadband assemblies, electromechanical components, electronic subsystems, tanks, and tubing. Serves the robotics, aerospace, agricultural, automotive, electrical, defense, food handling, medical, mining, and semiconductor industries.

Contract manufacturing services for custom designed components. Works with aluminum, stainless steel, carbon steel, hot rolled steel, cold rolled steel, galvanized steel, plastic and wood. Capabilities include rapid prototyping, engineering, electrical testing, toroidal and bobbin winding and transformer, electromechanical and electrical assembly. Secondary services such as packaging, shipping, distribution, slitting, annealing and coating are also provided. Prototype and low to high volume production runs available. Serves the aerospace, automotive, medical, power or current measurement, defense, electronics, industrial control and wiring device industries.

Manufacturer of cleaning machinery and head testers. Also, a remanufacturer of gearboxes, CMP equipment, chemical delivery systems, and metrology equipment. Capabilities include CNC machining, fabrication, 3D printing, and contract manufacturing. Works with aluminum, steel, stainless steel, cast alloys, titanium, and plastics. Prototype and production runs are available. On-site maintenance and repair services are also provided.

3, 4, 5 and 9-axis precision swiss, screw and vertical CNC machining services. Capabilities include milling, turning, shearing, routing, bending, assembly, drilling, tapping, sheet metal and plastic molded fabrication. Contract manufacturing, turret punching, sinker and wire EDM (electrical discharge machining) services are provided. Laser and waterjet cutting services are also offered. Works with aluminum, brass, stainless steel, copper, steel, nylon and PTFE materials. High production runs are available. Serves the energy, communication, automotive, sport, medical and aerospace industries. Secondary services include mechanical designing, reverse engineering, painting, powder coating, manual and tumbler deburring.

Manufacturer of connectors and electronic components for OEM applications. Available product selection includes connectors, cable assemblies, flexible circuits, battery and power supplies, and electro-mechanical assemblies. Stock and custom electronic products can be provided. Value-added services include design and engineering, PCB assembly, box build assembly, and laboratory testing services. Contract manufacturing services are available. Serves applications in the aerospace, energy, geophysical, industrial, instrumentation, marine, medical, military/defense, space exploration, storage/networking, and telecommunications industries.

Private label contract manufacturer of health, skin, beauty, and personal care products. Available in liquid, cream, gel, serum, and spray form. Nutraceutical supplements, vitamins, energy drinks, topicals, and weight loss products are offered. Body wash, sunscreens, lotions, deodorants, and shampoos are also available. Custom formulating services are provided. cGMP Compilant. FDA certified.

Contract manufacturer and assembly services specializing in the defense, aerospace, and semiconductor industries. Capabilities include CNC machining, lathe work, milling and four axis machining. Additional services include plating and painting. Production volume of medium complexity machined parts and assemblies. Works with aluminum, steel, brass, titanium, copper, plastics & other materials. Oil and gas and solar industries are also worked with.

Contract manufacturer of private label body, beauty, hair, skin, nail, sun and personal care products. Oils, creams, cleansers and lotions are available. Moisturizers, sunscreens, serums and gels are also offered. Secondary services include packaging. Made in the USA.

Contract manufacturing services. Capabilities include hydroforming, punch pressing (blanking, piercing, and drawing), metal spinning, roll forming, manual and CNC machining, laser cutting, wire EDM, and TIG and resistance welding. Machining capabilities include milling, drilling, boring, turning, deburring, grinding, knurling, polishing, reaming, and threading. Contract assembly and bonding services are also available. Secondary services include painting, marking, and chem film coating services. Materials worked with include aluminum, stainless steel, mild steel, high temperature alloys, mild steel, copper, brass, Inconel®, Hastelloy®, Hanes®, Waspaloy®, and titanium. Industries served include aerospace, defense/military, commercial, energy, and medical.

Private label manufacturer of health care products including powders and capsules. Contract manufacturing services are also provided. Totes, drums, bags, canisters and sachets packaging services are available. Additional services such as blending, encapsulation and label printing are also offered.

Contract manufacturing services for the aerospace, automotive, consumer product, healthcare and defense industries. Works with nylon. Tolerances of +/- 0.005 or +/- 0.002 per in. can be maintained. Capable of manufacturing parts with max print size of 380 x 284 x 380 mm, minimum print size of 3 x 3 x 3 mm, 0.08 mm layer height and dimensional accuracy of +/- 0.3% with a lower limit of +/- 0.3 mm. Vapor smoothing surface finish options available. Moving and assembled parts, cases, holders, adapters, cavities with design, sales, marketing and exhibition models, jewelry and art can be manufactured. Low volume to massive bulk order production offered. REACH and RoHS compliant. UL listed.
